# Widget Development Guide

**Last Updated:** November 19, 2025
**Status:** вң… Active
**Source:** Validated from codebase audit + Gemini analysis

---

## Overview

The Neuman Brain Dashboard features a modular widget system with 49+ widgets across 7 categories. This guide provides the complete specification for creating, registering, and deploying new dashboard widgets.

## Widget System Architecture

**Location:** `src/widgets/Dashboard/`

**Core Components:**
- **`BaseWidget.tsx`** - Reusable wrapper providing loading states, error handling, refresh buttons, and consistent styling
- **`WidgetRegistry.ts`** - Central registry mapping widget IDs to metadata, API configuration, and categories
- **Individual widget files** - Self-contained React components (e.g., `QuoteWidget.tsx`, `CryptoWidget.tsx`)

**Current Widget Count (Nov 2025):** 49 widgets
- **Core:** 2 widgets (Upcoming Events, Recent Notes)
- **Productivity:** 7 widgets (Quote, Pomodoro, Word of Day, Currency, World Clock, etc.)
- **News:** 7 widgets (Hacker News, Reddit, Dev.to, AI Research, Wikipedia, etc.)
- **Finance:** 3 widgets (Crypto, Stock Market)
- **Fun:** 5 widgets (Jokes, Facts, Bored, Memory Game, Typing Test)
- **Visual:** 1 widget (Weather Map)
- **Dev:** 8 widgets (GitHub, NPM Stats, GitHub Trending, Repo Stats, etc.)
- **Utility:** 16 widgets (IP Info, QR Code, Calculator, Unit Converter, Clipboard, etc.)

---

## Creating a Widget: Step-by-Step Guide

### Step 1: Create the Widget Component

Create a new file: `src/widgets/Dashboard/[WidgetName]Widget.tsx`

**Minimal Widget Template:**
```typescript
/**
 * [Widget Name] Widget
 *
 * [Brief description of what this widget does]
 */

import React, { useState, useEffect, useCallback } from 'react';
import { BaseWidget } from './BaseWidget';

export const MyNewWidget: React.FC = () => {
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);
  const [error, setError] = useState<string | null>(null);

  const fetchData = useCallback(async () => {
    setLoading(true);
    setError(null);

    try {
      // Your data fetching logic here
      setLoading(false);
    } catch (err) {
      setError(err instanceof Error ? err.message : 'Failed to load data');
      setLoading(false);
    }
  }, []);

  // Initial fetch
  useEffect(() => {
    fetchData();
  }, [fetchData]);

  return (
    <BaseWidget
      title="My Widget"
      icon="вҡЎ"
      loading={loading}
      error={error}
      onRefresh={fetchData}
    >
      {/* Your widget content here */}
      <div className="flex flex-col gap-2">
        <p className="text-text-light-primary dark:text-text-dark-primary">
          Widget content goes here
        </p>
      </div>
    </BaseWidget>
  );
};
```

### Step 2: Register the Widget

Add your widget to `src/widgets/Dashboard/WidgetRegistry.ts`:

```typescript
// 1. Import the widget component (at top of file)
import { MyNewWidget } from './MyNewWidget';

// 2. Add to WIDGET_REGISTRY object
export const WIDGET_REGISTRY: Record<string, WidgetDefinition> = {
  // ... existing widgets

  mynewwidget: {
    id: 'mynewwidget',
    name: 'My New Widget',
    description: 'Brief description for settings UI',
    icon: 'вҡЎ',
    category: 'utility', // core | productivity | news | finance | fun | visual | dev | utility
    apiUrl: 'https://api.example.com/endpoint', // Optional - only if using external API
    requiresAuth: false, // Set true if widget needs user configuration (API key, username)
    defaultEnabled: false, // Set true to auto-enable for new users
  },
};
```

### Step 3: Add to Dashboard Page

The widget will **automatically appear** in the Dashboard's widget selector once registered. No manual updates needed to `Dashboard.tsx`.

**How it works:**
- `Dashboard.tsx` reads `WIDGET_REGISTRY` at runtime
- User can enable/disable widgets from Settings
- Widget positions are saved to IndexedDB

---

## BaseWidget API Reference

The `BaseWidget` component provides a consistent wrapper for all dashboard widgets.

**Props:**
```typescript
interface BaseWidgetProps {
  title: string;           // Widget title (displays in header)
  icon: string;            // Emoji icon (displays next to title)
  children: React.ReactNode; // Widget content
  loading?: boolean;       // Shows loading spinner if true
  error?: string | null;   // Shows error message if not null
  onRefresh?: () => void;  // Refresh button handler (optional)
  onSettings?: () => void; // Settings button handler (optional)
  className?: string;      // Additional CSS classes (optional)
}
```

**Features Provided by BaseWidget:**
- вң… **Loading state** - Animated spinner with "Loading..." text
- вң… **Error handling** - User-friendly error display with retry button
- вң… **Refresh button** - Automatic refresh UI with spin animation
- вң… **Settings button** - Optional configuration UI
- вң… **Dark mode support** - Automatic theme switching
- вң… **Animations** - Smooth fade-in on mount (Framer Motion)
- вң… **Consistent styling** - Matches design system (surface colors, text colors, shadows)

**Example Usage:**
```typescript
<BaseWidget
  title="Weather Forecast"
  icon="рҹҢӨпёҸ"
  loading={isLoading}
  error={errorMessage}
  onRefresh={fetchWeather}
  onSettings={openSettingsModal}
>
  {/* Your widget content */}
</BaseWidget>
```

